The paper deals with influence diffusion and influence maximization in online social networks, which are topics that fall under the categories of social networks and computational social science. The paper also discusses the use of algorithms and simulations, which are relevant to the categories of data structures, artificial intelligence, and cybersecurity. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Computational Social Science), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CYBER (Computer Science and Game Theory).
